cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper deals with unsupervised learning on the outputs of a deep Convolutional Neural Network trained on the ImageNet of 1000 classes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of PCA and ICA, which are common techniques in machine learning and data analysis, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper proposes a new zero-shot learning method, which involves natural language processing, indicating that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper deals with neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
